- Aeropostale, Inc. (NYSE: ARO), a mall-based specialty retailer of casual and active apparel for young women and men, today announced that total net sales for the five-week period ended October 2, 2004 increased 18.3% to $90.6 million, compared to $76.6 million for the five-week period ended October 4, 2003. The company's comparable store sales increased 1.9% for the month, versus a comparable store sales increase of 22.0% in the year ago period.
New York, New York  October 6, 2004
Year-to-date, total net sales have increased 39.2% to $565.1 million, compared to $406.1 million in the year-ago period. Year to date, comparable store sales have increased 13.3%, compared to an increase of 7.3% in the year-ago period.
Julian R. Geiger, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer said, "During the month, we intentionally managed our business on leaner inventory levels despite a difficult comparison to the prior year. Accordingly, we are pleased that we generated positive comps for the period, while being less promotional and finishing the month with gross margins ahead of last year. We continue to be pleased with our merchandise assortment and are confident that we will be well positioned for the transition into the holiday selling season."
