ITEM 9.01 Financial Statements and Exhibits.
     C) Exhibits
          99.1 Press release, dated March 8, 2007, announcing February 2007 sales results.
 
     According to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the Registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned, thereunto duly authorized.
Dated: March 8, 2007

 
Exhibit 99.1
- Aeropostale, Inc. (NYSE: ARO), a mall-based specialty retailer of casual and active apparel for young women and men, today announced that total net sales for the four-week period ended March 3, 2007 increased 11.5% to $75.6 million, from $67.8 million for the four-week period ended February 25, 2006 and increased 11.0% on a pro-forma basis for the comparable four-week period last year. Same store sales for the month increased 2.3%, compared to the corresponding four-week period last year.
New York, New York  March 8, 2007
Julian R. Geiger, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer said, "We are pleased with our performance in February, despite a challenging retail environment. During the month, we experienced a solid reaction to our new spring merchandise, we had a strong increase in our gross margins, and we managed our promotional cadence. Our merchandise inventories are on plan, and we believe that our assortment is balanced and consistent with the fashion trends."
The company believes that the disclosure of net sales on a pro-forma basis, which is a non-GAAP financial measures, provides investors useful information to help them better understand the company's expected results.
To hear the Aeropostale prerecorded February sales message, please dial (877) 519-4471, followed by the conference identification number #8288610.
Aeropostale, Inc. is a mall-based, specialty retailer of casual apparel and accessories, principally targeting 14 to 17 year-old young women and men. The company provides customers with a focused selection of high-quality, active-oriented, fashion and fashion basic merchandise at compelling values. Aeropostale maintains control over its proprietary brands by designing, sourcing, marketing and selling all of its own merchandise. Aeropostale products are currently purchased only in its stores, on-line through its e-commerce website (www.aeropostale.com) or at organized sales events at college campuses.
About Aeropostale, Inc.
The company currently operates 728 Aeropostale stores in 47 states and 14 Jimmy'Z stores in 11 states.
