Exhibit 99.1
 
- Aeropostale, Inc. (NYSE: ARO), a mall-based specialty retailer of casual and active apparel for young women and men, today announced that total net sales for the five-week period ended April 3, 2010 increased 25% to $200.1 million, from $160.5 million for the five-week period ended April 4, 2009. The Company's same store sales increased 19% for the month, compared to a same store sales increase of 3% in the year ago period.
New York, New York  April 8, 2010
Year to date, total net sales have increased 21% to $326.5 million, from $270.4 million in the year-ago period. Year to date, same store sales have increased 14%, compared to a same store sales increase of 6% last year.
The Company stated that its performance reflected the continued strength of its spring merchandise assortment. The Company also noted that its results for the month include a positive impact due to the Easter calendar shift. In addition, merchandise margins for the month increased significantly over last year, and inventories remain well controlled and on plan.
Based on the stronger than expected results for the month, the Company now expects first quarter earnings of approximately $0.44 per diluted share, compared to its previously issued guidance of $0.39 to $0.40 per share. The revised guidance represents an increase of approximately 42% versus earnings of $0.31 per share last year.
To hear the Aeropostale prerecorded March sales message, please dial (866) 644-7738 or (585) 267-8033.
About Aropostale, Inc.
Aropostale, Inc. is a mall-based, specialty retailer of casual apparel and accessories, principally targeting 14 to 17 year-old young women and men through its Aropostale stores and 7 to 12 year-old kids through its P.S. from Aropostale stores. The Company provides customers with a focused selection of high-quality, active-oriented, fashion and fashion basic merchandise at compelling values. Aropostale maintains control over its proprietary brands by designing, sourcing, marketing and selling all of its own merchandise. Aropostale products can only be purchased in its Aropostale stores and online at www.aeropostale.com. P.S. from Aropostale products can be purchased in P.S. from Aropostale stores and online at www.ps4u.com. The Company currently oper ates 895 Aeropostale stores in 49 states and Puerto Rico, 44 Aeropostale stores in Canada and 16 P.S. from Aeropostale stores in 7 states.
