Exhibit 99.1
 
- Aropostale, Inc. (NYSE: ARO), a mall-based specialty retailer of casual and active apparel for young women and men, today announced that total net sales for the four-week period ended July 31, 2010 increased 6% to $166.7 million compared to $156.8 million for the four-week period ended August 1, 2009. The Companys same store sales increased 1% for the month, compared to a same store sales increase of 6% in the year ago period.
New York, New York  August 5, 2010
For the second quarter of fiscal 2010, total net sales increased 9% to $495.1 million, from $453.0 million in the year ago period. Same store sales for the second quarter increased 4%, compared to a same store sales increase of 12% last year.  Year to date, total net sales have increased 11% to $958.7 million, from $861.0 million in the year ago period. Year to date, same store sales have increased 5%, compared to a same store sales increase of 11% last year.
Second Quarter Guidance:
The Company now expects net earnings of $0.45 to $0.46 per share, versus $0.38 per share last year, due primarily to the challenging retail environment, in addition to a change in consumer shopping behaviors. This updated guidance is within its previously issued guidance of $0.45 to $0.48 per share.
To hear the Aropostale prerecorded July sales message, please dial (866) 644-7738 or (585) 267-8033.
About Aropostale, Inc.
Aropostale, Inc. is a mall-based, specialty retailer of casual apparel and accessories, principally targeting 14 to 17 year-old young women and men through its Aropostale stores and 7 to 12 year-old kids through its P.S. from Aropostale stores. The Company provides customers with a focused selection of high-quality, active-oriented, fashion and fashion basic merchandise at compelling values. Aropostale maintains control over its proprietary brands by designing, sourcing, marketing and selling all of its own merchandise. Aropostale products can only be purchased in its Aropostale stores and online at www.aeropostale.com. P.S. from Aropostale products can be purchased in P.S. from Aropostale stores and online at www.ps4u.com. The Company currently operate s 902 Aropostale stores in 49 states and Puerto Rico, 46 Aropostale stores in Canada and 35 P.S. from Aropostale stores in 12 states.
