Exhibit 99.1
 
- Aropostale, Inc. (NYSE: ARO), a mall-based specialty retailer of casual and active apparel for young women and men, today announced that total net sales for the five-week period ended January 1, 2011 increased 3% to $474.7 million, from $460.8 million for the five-week period ended January 2, 2010. The Companys same store sales decreased 5% for the month, compared to a same store sales increase of 10% in the year ago period.
New York, New York  January 6, 2011
Year to date, total net sales have increased 8% to $2.280 billion, from $2.118 billion in the year ago period. Year to date, same store sales have increased 1%, compared to a same store sales increase of 10% last year.
The Company stated that it executed its promotional plan throughout the month, while navigating through a highly competitive Holiday selling season. Accordingly, the Company is reiterating its previously issued fourth quarter guidance range of approximately $0.94 to $0.96 per diluted share.
